'''Google Inc.''' ({{nasdaq|GOOG}}, {{FWB|GGQ1}}) is a [[multinational corporation|multinational]] [[Public company|public]] [[cloud computing]] and [[Internet search]] technologies [[corporation]]. Google hosts and develops [[List of Google products|a number]] of [[Internet]]-based services and products, and generates profit primarily from [[advertising]] through its [[AdWords]] program.<ref name="financialtables">{{cite web |url=http://investor.google.com/fin_data.html |title=Financial Tables |publisher=Google Investor Relations |accessdate=2008-01-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Online Ads Give Google Huge Gain in Profit |author=David A. Vise |url=David A. Vise |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2005-10-21 |accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref> The company was founded by [[Larry Page]] and [[Sergey Brin]], often dubbed the "[[Google Guys]]",<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,1158956,00.html|title=Meet the Google Guys|last=Ignatius|first=Adi|date=2006-02-12|work=Time Magazine|publisher=Time Inc.|accessdate=27 March 2010|location=San Francisco, CA}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/video/watch/?id=4835250n&tag=mncol;lst;1|title=The Google Guys|date=2009-03-12|newspaper=CBS News.com|publisher=CBS Interactive|accessdate=27 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://gizmodo.com/5464532/google-wants-to-add-store-interiors-to-maps|title=Google Wants to Add Store Interiors to Maps|last=Barrett|first=Brian|date=2010-02-04|publisher=Gizmodo|accessdate=27 March 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/business/google_guys_to_sell_stock_nRuRNTxYhkEi0Eo1JaEYGI|title=Google guys to sell stock|date=2010-01-24|newspaper=New York Post|publisher=NYP Holdings|accessdate=27 March 2010|location=San Francisco|agency=Associated Press}}</ref> while the two were attending [[Stanford University]] as Ph.D. candidates. It was first incorporated as a [[privately held company]] on September 4, 1998, with its [[initial public offering]] to follow on August 19, 2004. The company's [[mission statement|stated mission]] from the outset was "to organize the world's information and make it universally accessible and useful",<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.google.com/corporate/ |title=Google Corporate Information |publisher=Google, Inc. |accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref> and the company's unofficial slogan{{ndash}} coined by Google engineer [[Paul Buchheit]]{{ndash}} is ''[[Don't be evil]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://investor.google.com/conduct.html |title=Google Code of Conduct |date=2009-04-08 |publisher=Google, Inc. |accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogoscoped.com/archive/2007-07-16-n55.html |title=Paul Buchheit on Gmail, AdSense and More |first=Philip|last=Lenssen |date=2007-07-16 |publisher=Google Blogscoped |accessdate=2010-02-14}}</ref> In 2006, the company moved to their current [[Googleplex|headquarters]] in [[Mountain View, California]].
